# Patterns to Avoid

## Fills and Canvas

- **Never replace a gradient fill with a solid fill when updating opacity.** Opacity changes must shallow-copy the existing fill and only update `.opacity`. The fill type, stops, angle, etc. must be preserved.
- **Never read `.color` from a gradient fill.** Gradient fills have `.stops`, not `.color`. Always check `fill.type` before accessing type-specific properties.
- **Never hardcode `type: "solid"` in generic fill mutation paths.** Build the new fill from the existing one.
- **Never create a new `nanoid()` for a fill when only updating a property.** Spread the existing fill to preserve its `id`.
- **Never hardcode `opacity: 1` when creating a fill from a control change.** Always read `obj.fills?.[0]?.opacity ?? 1` to preserve the user's current opacity setting. Every fill mutation path (gradient, hex, RGB) must carry forward the existing opacity.

## Gen-AI

- **Never use `color` type controls for gradients.** Always use `fill` (type `"fill"`) for any gradient, multi-stop, or fill control. The `color` type is strictly for single solid colors.
- **Never discard `genAiSpec` when re-running a generator.** The stamped spec (with `props.defaultValue` set) is the source of truth. Always stamp current values before persisting.
- **Never let the LLM's `defaultValue` overwrite a stamped `defaultValue` during merge.** When `replace: false`, if a control already exists in the previous spec with a stamped `defaultValue`, always carry it forward. The LLM doesn't know the user's current runtime value.
- **Never assume the LLM will produce `createFrame` as root.** Add defensive fallbacks in `rewriteActionsForReapply` for bare `createRectangle` / `createEllipse` root actions.
- **Never use a single global chat history for all gen-ai conversations.** Chat history is scoped per frame ID (`chatHistoryMapRef`). Switching frames must not leak conversation context.
- **Never store auto-generate exchanges in chat history.** Auto-generate is one-shot; its response should not influence follow-up prompts.
- **Never use `xy-pad` for width/height controls.** Use separate sliders. `xy-pad` is only for 2D offsets or positions.
- **Never use `axisLabels` on xy-pad controls.** The prop was removed. The pad only shows built-in X/Y numeric inputs.
- **Never set `size` on a control unless the user explicitly requests it.** All controls default to `"large"`. The LLM must not auto-assign `"xl"` to xy-pad or any other type.
- **Never clear `rootFrameIdRef` on `replace: true` when `targetObjectId` is set.** Auto-generate targets an existing object; `replace: true` must not wipe the target reference.

## CSS / Styling

- **Never use `!important` in Tailwind utilities.** Manage specificity through CSS `@layer` ordering and scoped selectors (`.figui3-scope`).
- **Never apply Tailwind `text-*` or `leading-*` classes inside `.figui3-scope`.** FigUI3 components have their own sizing; override only via `figui3-scoped.css`.
- **Never apply global font-size resets that affect FigUI3 web components.** Use the `.figui3-scope` boundary.

## State

- **Never mutate Zustand store state directly.** Always go through `dispatch`.
- **Never store high-frequency update state (drag, resize positions) in the main Immer store.** Use `transientStore`.
- **Never `JSON.parse` without a try/catch.** Persisted `genAiSpec` and `genAiValues` can be malformed.

## React

- **Never set FigUI3 web component properties via React props that map to getters (read-only).** Use imperative DOM creation (`document.createElement`, `setAttribute`) instead.
- **Never use `useEffect` with the full `spec` object as a dependency.** Use a stable key like `controlStructureKey` (derived from control IDs and types) to avoid unnecessary re-initializations.
